<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Blargg's NTSC filter demo for Windows]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11947&amp;p=135501#p135501"><![CDATA[
That's not unclear at all:<br /><br />In OpenGL, 0 is a pixel corner.<br />In Direct3D &lt;= 9, 0 is a pixel centre (i.e. the wrong way to do it).<br />In Direct3D &gt;= 10, 0 is configurable as either but defaults to the pixel corner.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> — Fri Oct 24, 2014 6:26 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
