I'd say that the 602×448 image probably shouldn't have been downscaled at all in the first place... I mean, artifacts vary at the subpixel level, so the higher resolution is actually needed for an accurate representation. Not to mention that let's face it, it's not a large image for today's resolutions (heck, for the current higher resolutions 256×224 is actually too small).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4526">Sik</a> — Thu Oct 23, 2014 4:34 pm</p><hr />
